<div id=3D"outline-container-orgd437003" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"orgd437003">Coordination with the OCaml Users and Developers Work=
shop</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-orgd437003">
<p>
The OCaml workshop is seen as more practical and is dedicated in=20
significant part to OCaml community building and the development of=20
the OCaml system. In contrast, the ML family workshop is not focused=20
on any language in particular, is more research-oriented, and deals=20
with general issues of ML-style programming and type systems. There=20
is some overlap, which we are keen to explore in various ways. The=20
authors who feel their submission fits both workshops are encouraged=20
to mention it at submission time or contact the program chairs.
</p>
</div>
