<div id=3D"outline-container-org263665b" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"org263665b">fantazio announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-org263665b">
<p>
Hello everyone,
</p>

<p>
I am happy to announce <a href=3D"https://github.com/LexiFi/dead_code_analy=
zer/releases">2 releases of the dead_code_analyzer</a> (available via <code=
>opam</code>) :
</p>

<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>Release <a href=3D"https://github.com/LexiFi/dead_code_analyzer/release=
s/tag/1.1.1">1.1.1</a> includes a number of bug fixes and strengthens seman=
tics. It also improves the <a href=3D"https://github.com/LexiFi/dead_code_a=
nalyzer/blob/1.1.1/docs/USER_DOC.md">user documentation</a> by describing e=
ach report section, their usage and limitations with examples. This release=
 is compatible with <b><b>OCaml 5.2</b></b>.</li>

<li>Release <a href=3D"https://github.com/LexiFi/dead_code_analyzer/release=
s/tag/1.2.0">1.2.0</a> is an update of 1.1.1, compatible with <b><b>OCaml 5=
.3</b></b>. The analyzer now takes <code>.cmti</code> and <code>.cmt</code>=
 files as input instead of <code>.cmi</code> and <code>.cmt</code>. You may=
 notice a larger memory consumption (more information available <a href=3D"=
https://github.com/LexiFi/dead_code_analyzer/pull/38">here</a>).</li>
</ul>

<p>
I addition to these releases, a version compatible with <b><b>OCaml 4.14</b=
></b> is <a href=3D"https://github.com/fantazio/dead_code_analyzer/tree/4.1=
4">available on my fork</a>.
</p>

<p>
Thanks to the <a href=3D"https://ocaml-sf.org/">OCaml Software Foundation</=
a> its funding!
</p>

<p>
If you encounter any issue with these releases, please <a href=3D"https://g=
ithub.com/LexiFi/dead_code_analyzer/issues">report it on the github reposit=
ory</a>.
Feedback and contributions are welcome.
</p>
